  "market_context": "On the 4-hour chart, NQ hit a bearish target from a candle two closure into a fair value gap around 22575-22500. On the new 4H open, a candle three closure formed by closing over the body of candle two, signalling a bullish reversal. Drilled down to the 15-minute chart for entry framing.",
  "key_observation": "The 15-minute price action reached into a fair value gap and closed over the down-close bodies, producing a change in state of delivery and establishing a protected swing low that could be used as stop placement for a long entry in the upper half of the prior 4H candle.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the 4H bearish candle two closure hitting its target into the prior 4H fair value gap zone.",
    "Step 2: On the new 4H open, recognized a candle three closure where price closed over the body of candle two, marking the reversal point.",
    "Step 3: Marked the full range of the prior 4H candle and required the upper half to be respected for a bullish setup.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to the 15-minute chart to frame the entry, using the indicator to identify structure.",
    "Step 5: Observed price reaching into a 15m fair value gap and closing over the series of down-close bodies, confirming a change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 6: Defined the protected swing low from this CISD and expected it to hold.",
    "Step 7: Planned entry in the upper half of the prior 4H candle with stop on the protected swing low, targeting at least 2R."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade achieved 2R as planned, with price continuing higher afterward.",
  "lessons": "Filtering swing points using candle two and candle three closures with a valid point of interest, then dropping to a lower timeframe to locate a protected swing via CISD, allows precise entries with tight stops capable of hitting 2R targets.",
